al principles saves time, reduces frustration, and provides the flexibility to tackle any visualization challenge with confidence!"]})]}),moduleNumber:1,toc:[{name:"Why R and ggplot2?",title:"Crafting Data Visualizations: Why R and ggplot2?",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:["What makes ",(0,t.jsx)("code",{children:"ggplot2"})," different — and why should you choose it over tools like Excel or Tableau? This lesson dives into what sets ",(0,t.jsx)("code",{children:"R"})," and ",(0,t.jsx)("code",{children:"ggplot2"})," apart when it comes to"," ",(0,t.jsx)("b",{children:"customization, reproducibility, and the power of code"}),"."]}),(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:["Let's get a clear sense of when and why to reach for"," ",(0,t.jsx)("code",{children:"ggplot2"})," — and how it fits into the broader data visualization landscape."]})]}),url:"/module1/why-ggplot",isFree:!0,isAvailable:!0,time:5,exoNumber:0},{name:"Principles of ggplot2",title:"Principles of ggplot2: Understanding Components",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:["Unlike many other charting libraries, ",(0,t.jsx)("code",{children:"ggplot2"})," doesn’t provide functions for specific chart types like"," ",(0,t.jsx)("code",{children:"scatterplot()"})," or",(0,t.jsx)("code",{children:"boxplot()"}),". Instead, it follows the grammar of graphics: a structured yet flexible approach where"," ",(0,t.jsx)("b",{children:"plots are built from components"})," like sentences from words."]}),(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"Let’s look at how this “sentence-building” approach works — and why it’s such a powerful way to visualize data!"})]}),url:"/module1/principles",isFree:!0,isAvailable:!0,time:6,exoNumber:6},{name:"Aesthetics: Fundamentals",title:"Aesthetics: Mapping Data to Visual Properties",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:["Every plot in ",(0,t.jsx)("code",{children:"ggplot2"})," begins with aesthetic mappings:"," ",(0,t.jsx)("b",{children:"which variables you want to show, and how"})," you want to represent them visually."]}),(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"In this lesson, you’ll learn how to map data to position, color, size, shape, and more — and how these choices influence how your audience reads and interprets your plot."}),(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:["For a quick overview of available aesthetics and usage examples, check out the ",(0,t.jsx)(i.default,{href:"#explorer",children:"aesthetics explorer"})," ","widget at the end of the lesson!"]})]}),url:"/module1/aesthetics",isFree:!1,isAvailable:!0,time:10,exoNumber:6},{name:"Aesthetics: Caveats",title:"Aesthetics: Handling Caveats When Mapping Variables",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:["Aesthetic mappings are powerful — but they can sometimes produce"," ",(0,t.jsx)("b",{children:"unexpected results"}),". In this session, we’ll explore"," ",(0,t.jsx)("b",{children:"common pitfalls"})," that trip up even experienced users — from missing legends to confusing lines or plots that just don’t “look right.”"]}),(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:["You’ll learn to spot, understand, and fix these issues — so you can ",(0,t.jsx)("b",{children:"debug your plots with confidence"})," and avoid frustration down the line."]})]}),url:"/module1/aesthetics-caveats",isFree:!1,isAvailable:!0,time:8,exoNumber:5},{name:"Geometric Layers",title:"Geometric Layers: Choosing the Visual Representation",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"Bars, lines, points, and beyond — geometric layers define how your data appears on your panel. Think of them as the “verbs” in your visualization sentence."}),(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"This lesson explores how to pick the right geom for the job and how different layers can be combined to tell richer, more nuanced stories."})]}),url:"/module1/geoms",isFree:!1,isAvailable:!0,time:11,exoNumber:5},{name:"Statistical Layers",title:"Statistical Layers: Transforming Data Before Plotting",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:["Every geom in ",(0,t.jsx)("code",{children:"ggplot2"})," applies a statistical transformation to processes your raw data before plotting. So far, you’ve mostly used geoms and let their default stats do the work behind the scenes. But sometimes, the defaults are not what you need."]}),(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:["In this lesson, we’ll explore how to"," ",(0,t.jsx)("b",{children:"explicitly control statistical transformations"})," in layers. Understanding the link between geoms and stats — and when to switch or customize them — helps you create clearer, more advanced visualizations."]})]}),url:"/module1/stats",isFree:!1,isAvailable:!0,time:6,exoNumber:5},{name:"Coordinate Systems",title:"Coordinate Systems: Setting the Stage for Your Plot",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"Coordinate systems determine how data is projected onto the plotting canvas. They influence the layout, orientation, and even the perceived shape of your geometries."}),(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:["From the brand-new ",(0,t.jsx)("code",{children:"coord_radial()"})," to flexible options like ",(0,t.jsx)("code",{children:"coord_trans()"}),", you'll learn how different coordinate systems can reshape your plot — and your perspective on your data."]})]}),url:"/module1/coordinates",isFree:!1,isAvailable:!0,time:5,exoNumber:5},{name:"Scales",title:"Scales: Defining How Data is Mapped to Aesthetics",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"Scales determine how raw data gets converted into colors, sizes, axes, and more. They’re the link between data values and their visual representation."}),(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"From color palettes to log transforms, you’ll learn how to take full control over the look and feel of your plots — without changing the data itself."})]}),url:"/module1/scales",isFree:!1,isAvailable:!0,time:9,exoNumber:6},{name:"Exporting Plots",title:"Exporting Plots: Saving High-Quality Graphics",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"You've crafted your viusalization — now what? Time to share it! This lesson covers how to export high-quality graphics from R for papers, slides, or social media."}),(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"Learn which formats to choose, how to control resolution, and what to watch out for when saving plots across platforms."})]}),url:"/module1/export",isFree:!0,isAvailable:!0,time:6,exoNumber:0},{name:"Project",title:"Your Turn: Real-World Project",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:[(0,t.jsx)("span",{className:"simple-highlight-teal",children:" Congrats! "})," ","🥳 You’ve completed the first module! You now have a clear understanding of what ggplot2 is and how to create and save your own charts."]}),(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"Now, let's put this knowledge into practice with real-world datasets, before we take your skills to the next level! 🚀"})]}),url:"/module1/project",isFree:!1,isAvailable:!0,time:20,exoNumber:0}]},{name:"Customization & Styling",color:"var(--set1-orange)",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:["Learn how to customize and style visualizations to make them clear, accessible, and publication-ready. You'll explore themes for consistent design, fine-tune ",(0,t.jsx)("code",{children:"scale_*()"})," functions, customize color palettes, and enhance legends to ensure your plots align with your specific needs and branding."]}),(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:[(0,t.jsx)("b",{children:"Creating polished visualizations will allow you to leave a lasting impression 🎨"}),(0,t.jsx)("br",{}),"Moving beyond default settings will help you craft charts that are not only informative but also visually compelling, consistent, and professionally designed!"]})]}),moduleNumber:2,toc:[{name:"Complete Themes",title:"Complete Themes: Quickly Change the Style of Your Plots",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:["Themes control the ",(0,t.jsx)("b",{children:"overall style"})," of your plots — from typefaces and font settings to grid lines, backgrounds, and margins. They’re what make a chart feel clean, polished, and consistent."]}),(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:["In this lesson, you’ll learn how to apply and adjust complete themes to give your plots a ",(0,t.jsx)("b",{children:"cohesive look"})," without touching the underlying data or mappings. By the end, you’ll know how to switch between built-in themes, customize them, and make your charts presentation-ready with just a few lines of code."]})]}),url:"/module2/complete-themes",isFree:!0,isAvailable:!0,time:4,exoNumber:2},{name:"Custom Themes",title:"Custom Themes: Fine-Tune Your Plot's Appearance",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:["In the"," ",(0,t.jsx)(i.default,{href:"/module2/complete-themes",children:"previous lesson"}),", we explored how to use complete themes. But to create a true visual identity, you need to know how to ",(0,t.jsx)("b",{children:"customize themes"}),"."]}),(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:["It's time to dive deep into the"," ",(0,t.jsx)("b",{children:(0,t.jsx)("code",{children:"theme()"})})," ","function and learn how to modify every aspect of your charts. Let's forget the defaults and make your visuals match your brand and publication style!"]})]}),url:"/module2/custom-themes",isFree:!1,isAvailable:!0,time:7,exoNumber:4},{name:"Color Choice",title:"Color Choice: Picking Palettes with Purpose",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:["Great visualizations don’t use color just for decoration — they use it to ",(0,t.jsx)("b",{children:"clarify, emphasize, and guide"}),". Effective color choices make your plots readable, accurate, and inclusive. Choosing colors thoughtfully helps avoid misleading impressions and highlights the patterns that matter most."]}),(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:["This ",(0,t.jsx)("b",{children:"no-code lesson focusses on how to choose colors"})," with both purpose and accessibility in mind: selecting well-designed palettes, ensuring color-blind safety and sufficient contrast, and applying principles that make visualizations clearer and more reliable for everyone."]})]}),url:"/module2/color-choice",isFree:!1,isAvailable:!0,time:9,exoNumber:0},{name:"Color Palettes",title:"Color Palettes: Moving Beyond ggplot2 Defaults",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:["Colors are one of the most powerful tools to tell a story with your data. In this lesson, you’ll use color to highlight patterns, reinforce categories, and make your plots more readable — all while moving beyond",(0,t.jsx)("code",{children:"ggplot2"}),"’s default palettes."]}),(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:["You’ll explore built-in palettes, learn to tweak scales for impact, and discover popular community palettes like",(0,t.jsx)("code",{children:"viridis"})," and ",(0,t.jsx)("code",{children:"RColorBrewer"}),". Along the way, you’ll also see how to craft custom palettes, giving you full flexibility without getting lost in options."]})]}),url:"/module2/palettes",isFree:!1,isAvailable:!0,time:13,exoNumber:7},{name:"Legend Styling",title:"Legend Styling: Highlight What Matters",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:["Legends bridge the gap between ",(0,t.jsx)("b",{children:"data"})," and ",(0,t.jsx)("b",{children:"perception"})," — they help viewers decode colors, shapes, and lines at a glance. But a cluttered or confusing legend can break that connection fast."]}),(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:["You’ll learn how to customize legend placement, direction, titles, spacing, and keys with ",(0,t.jsx)("code",{children:"guides()"})," and"," ",(0,t.jsx)("code",{children:"theme()"}),". By the end, your legends will complement your story instead of competing with it."]})]}),url:"/module2/legend-styling",isFree:!1,isAvailable:!0,time:12,exoNumber:8},{name:"Project",title:"Your Turn: Real-World Project",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:[(0,t.jsx)("span",{className:"simple-highlight-teal",children:" Congrats! "})," ","🥳 You’ve completed the second module! You now know how to customize a chart to make it pretty and aligned with your brand."]}),(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"Now, let's put this knowledge into practice with real-world datasets, before we take your skills to the next level! 🚀"})]}),url:"/module2/project",isFree:!1,isAvailable:!0,time:20,exoNumber:0}]},{name:"Labels, Titles & Annotations",color:"var(--set1-gold)",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:["This module covers techniques to enhance readability and communication in your plots. You’ll learn to add informative titles, captions, and annotations, use smart text placement with ",(0,t.jsx)("code",{children:"ggrepel"})," and"," ",(0,t.jsx)("code",{children:"geomtextpath"}),", and explore advanced text rendering options for better storytelling."]}),(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:[(0,t.jsx)("b",{children:"Elevate your storytelling techniques by crafting charts that not just show data—but guide your audience with clarity 🎯"}),(0,t.jsx)("br",{}),"Clear and well-placed text elements make your visualizations more engaging, helping viewers understand key insights at a glance."]})]}),moduleNumber:3,toc:[{name:"Titles & Captions",title:"Titles & Captions: Adding Context to Your Plots",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"A strong title can turn a good chart into a clear message. Subtitles, captions, and tags provide context, guide interpretation, and make your visual narrative easier to follow."}),(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"In this lesson, you’ll learn how to craft effective titles and apply best-practice principles for hierarchy and clarity. We’ll cover all label options that are available and demonstrate practical styling techniques to make titles, subtitles, and captions feel intentional and well-balanced."})]}),url:"/module3/titles-captions",isFree:!0,isAvailable:!0,time:9,exoNumber:0},{name:"Annotations & Callouts",title:"Annotations & Callouts: Guiding the Viewer with Additional Insights",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"Sometimes the story lives in a single point, line, or trend — and annotations help you draw attention to it. They turn raw data into clear communication."}),(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:["You’ll explore ",(0,t.jsx)("code",{children:"annotate()"}),", ",(0,t.jsx)("code",{children:"geom_text()"}),", and ",(0,t.jsx)("code",{children:"geom_label()"})," for direct text notes, along with arrows, boxes, and shapes to call out important findings. Learn to emphasize without overwhelming."]})]}),url:"/module3/annotations",isFree:!1,isAvailable:!0,time:9,exoNumber:7},{name:"Smart Label Placement",title:"Smart Label Placement: Minimizing Effort for Clear Annotations",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"Well-placed labels guide the eye, instantly clarifying patterns and reducing the mental effort required to understand a plot. But manually positioning them often involves tedious fine-tuning to avoid overlaps, highlight certain groups, or craft callouts that look professional."}),(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"In this lesson, you’ll learn to automate label placement using smart tools that handle the heavy lifting for you. You’ll master techniques for annotating points, lines, and groups — ensuring your callouts remain readable, organized, and professional with far less effort."})]}),url:"/module3/smart-labels",isFree:!1,isAvailable:!0,time:9,exoNumber:8},{name:"Text Styling",title:"Text Styling: Advanced Formatting and Rendering Techniques",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"Standard plot text is usually rigid and uniform, making it difficult to highlight key takeaways or build advanced layouts. Basic text elements simply aren't built to handle complex structures like varying text formats, lists, or embedded images."}),(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:["In this lesson, you’ll explore ",(0,t.jsx)("code",{children:"ggtext"})," and"," ",(0,t.jsx)("code",{children:"marquee"})," to render Markdown and rich-text directly into your plots. You’ll learn to emphasize specific words, replace clunky legends with clear descriptions, and integrate advanced elements like lists, code chunks, and images."]})]}),url:"/module3/styling-text",isFree:!1,isAvailable:!0,time:9,exoNumber:6},{name:"Project",title:"Your Turn: Real-World Project",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:[(0,t.jsx)("span",{className:"simple-highlight-teal",children:" Congrats! "})," ","🥳 You’ve completed the third module! Labels, annotations, and text highlights are a core part of a great chart and you now are able mastering them with R and ggplot2."]}),(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"Now, let's put this knowledge into practice with real-world datasets, before we move on to module 4."})]}),url:"/module3/project",isFree:!1,isAvailable:!0,time:20,exoNumber:0}]},{name:"Plot Composition",color:"var(--set1-teal)",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"This module teaches you how to arrange multiple plots into a coherent narrative. You'll learn about small multiples, advanced faceting techniques, and multi-plot layouts to structure visualizations effectively."}),(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:[(0,t.jsx)("b",{children:"Learning to structure multiple plots effectively will transform your visualizations into a compelling narrative 📚"}),(0,t.jsx)("br",{}),"Mastering plot composition allows you to showcase trends, compare categories, and communicate complex insights with clarity."]})]}),moduleNumber:4,toc:[{name:"Small Multiples",title:"Small Multiples: Comparing Subsets with Facets",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"Small multiples, also known as facets, are a powerful way to compare patterns across groups by repeating the same chart for different subsets of your data. Instead of squeezing everything into a single crowded panel, you can lay out a grid of consistent plots that make similarities and differences easier to spot at a glance."}),(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"In this lesson, you’ll learn how to use faceting to break data into meaningful subsets, control the layout and scales of your panels, and decide when small multiples are the right tool for your story."})]}),url:"/module4/small-multiples",isFree:!0,isAvailable:!0,time:9,exoNumber:8},{name:"Hierarchical Facets",title:"Hierarchical Facets: Advanced Layouts for Small Multiples",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"Many real-world datasets aren’t flat — they’re organized into nested groups such as regions within country, products within broader categories, or species within a genus or family. Hierarchical facets help you reflect this structure directly in your visualizations, so viewers can navigate complex groupings without getting lost."}),(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"In this lesson, you’ll learn how to build multi-level facet layouts, customize strip labels to keep them readable and informative, and use nested structures to clarify relationships between groups."})]}),url:"/module4/facets-advanced",isFree:!1,isAvailable:!1,time:9,exoNumber:4},{name:"Multi-Plot Layouts",title:"Multi-Plot Layouts: The Composition of Charts",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"Small multiples and facets work wonders when repeating the same chart structure, but sometimes you need different views working together: an overview alongside focused detail, or complementary charts revealing distinct angles of the same data."}),(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"In this lesson, you'll learn how to combine plots from basic side-by-side arrangements to complex layouts. You'll practice controlling spacing and whitespace, adding overarching titles and clever tags, and placing inset charts with precise alignment to build visual hierarchy and intuitive flow."})]}),url:"/module4/plot-layouts",isFree:!1,isAvailable:!1,time:9,exoNumber:4}]},{name:"Visualizing Spatial Data",color:"var(--set1-purple)",description:(0,t.jsxs)(t.Fragment,{children:[(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:["This module covers the essentials of working with spatial data in"," ",(0,t.jsx)("code",{children:"ggplot2"}),"and ",(0,t.jsx)("code",{children:"sf"}),". You’ll learn how to create maps, customize spatial layers, and fine-tune geographic visualizations for effective storytelling."]}),(0,t.jsxs)("p",{children:[(0,t.jsx)("b",{children:"Building spatial visualizations helps you explore geographic insights and reveal meaningful patterns 🗺️"}),(0,t.jsx)("br",{}),"Whether you’re analyzing geographic trends or presenting location-based insights, learning how to create well-designed spatial visualizations allows you to add depth and clarity to your data."]})]}),moduleNumber:5,toc:[{name:"Spatial Data",title:"Spatial Data: The Basics of Geospatial Information",description:(0,t.jsx)(t.Fragment,{children:(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"Work in progress"})}),url:"/module6/spatial-data",isFree:!1,isAvailable:!1,time:9,exoNumber:4},{name:"Maps with ggplot2",title:"Maps with ggplot2: Plotting Geospatial Data",description:(0,t.jsx)(t.Fragment,{children:(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"Work in progress"})}),url:"/module6/maps-basics",isFree:!1,isAvailable:!1,time:9,exoNumber:4},{name:"Customizing Maps",title:"Customizing Maps: Enhancing Spatial Visualization",description:(0,t.jsx)(t.Fragment,{children:(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"Work in progress"})}),url:"/module6/maps-custom",isFree:!1,isAvailable:!1,time:9,exoNumber:4},{name:"Tile Grid Maps",title:"Tile Grid Maps: Creating Spatial Small Multiples",description:(0,t.jsx)(t.Fragment,{children:(0,t.jsx)("p",{children:"Work in progress"})}),url:"/module6/spatial-data",isFree:!1,isAvailable:!1,time:9,exoNumber:4}]},{name:"Interactivity & Animation",color:"var(--set1